This monumental lexicon (abbreviated LGG) collects the names, titles, and attestations of many Egyptian gods and goddesses, together with other entities which we can fairly confidentially label as ‘demons’. Each lemma is structured the same way: after the lemma and its variants, it follows the dating of the attested terms, the reference of epithets to specific deities, the function and attributes of the god/goddess in different contexts, sometimes the iconography on reliefs or other supports, and finally the references to original sources.    

